docs.text:
Personal information part


Presentation


Hi, I'm Romain Bizzari. I achive a Scientific bacalaurea in Briey, very little town close to Metz. Then I went to Nancy for 2 years of intensive courses. a l'issu d'un concours which allow me to study physics.   I am passionated on new technology and understand physics that why I meet both thanks to computation fluids dynamics. 


In currently PhD student at CERFACS (European Center for Research and Advanced Training in Scientific Computation). 
I am specialist in fluids mecanics and computation fluid dynamics on HPC (High performance computing) and massively parralel application. 


Now I am turning to industial case where many physicals phenomens are involved.

docs.text:
Rotative detonative engine


The last 6 month of my ingeneering school was an internship. I choose to work on a rotative detonative engine at CERFACS. This internship should result on a PhD. However since the funding was granted by Safran they decided to not fund this PhD. However this 6 month was very interesting.
